1
00:00:00,292 --> 00:00:04,167
What I know is this was only an information office

2
00:00:04,959 --> 00:00:07,209
And that was the interrogation room

3
00:00:07,959 --> 00:00:09,876
As for the other rooms, I don’t know what’s inside

4
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,500
We don’t know what’s inside them, we only know ISIS were here

5
00:00:14,876 --> 00:00:16,542
But we don’t know what these rooms are

6
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:20,250
Interviewer: When you entered this place

7
00:00:20,292 --> 00:00:22,918
Did you see ISIS members you knew?

8
00:00:23,042 --> 00:00:27,626
Or did you see people brought here to be imprisoned

9
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:30,083
Who were your friends or people you knew?

10
00:00:32,292 --> 00:00:35,959
Yes there were, but we didn’t know the ISIS members

11
00:00:37,125 --> 00:00:40,918
The ones who were here, the ones standing here

12
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,000
And the one sitting here, the one inside

13
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:44,876
They were ISIS we didn’t know

14
00:00:45,167 --> 00:00:47,959
But the prisoners they brought in, we knew of course

15
00:00:48,042 --> 00:00:49,417
Because they were all from the area

16
00:00:50,209 --> 00:00:52,125
You’d see someone they’d brought from the market

17
00:00:52,542 --> 00:00:56,876
Another of your neighbors, another from a bit further away they also brought

18
00:00:57,709 --> 00:00:58,876
They imprisoned them with you

19
00:00:58,918 --> 00:01:03,959
Some of my friends were imprisoned with me, and my neighbors too

20
00:01:06,125 --> 00:01:10,918
But we didn’t know the ISIS members

21
00:01:12,959 --> 00:01:14,167
We didn’t know any of them

22
00:01:14,751 --> 00:01:16,959
Interviewer: How were the sounds and the atmosphere?

23
00:01:16,959 --> 00:01:19,584
What were they talking about and in what language?

24
00:01:20,667 --> 00:01:22,292
Did they shout for example?

25
00:01:22,417 --> 00:01:27,209
Did they play their jihadi chants?

26
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:31,209
For me, when I came here for interrogation

27
00:01:31,584 --> 00:01:33,667
Only their voices could be heard

28
00:01:34,709 --> 00:01:38,459
But in the prison hall in the other building

29
00:01:38,667 --> 00:01:41,584
Which was in the church behind us, their prison

30
00:01:42,334 --> 00:01:43,542
You could hear voices there

31
00:01:44,292 --> 00:01:47,375
You’d hear the sound of torture here, and there someone being whipped

32
00:01:48,167 --> 00:01:50,500
And over there someone being interrogated and beaten

33
00:01:51,751 --> 00:01:53,417
But we didn’t know who they were

34
00:01:55,083 --> 00:01:59,083
For me, when I was imprisoned in this place

35
00:01:59,584 --> 00:02:01,250
And now I look at it again

36
00:02:01,417 --> 00:02:02,876
Honestly I can’t believe this

37
00:02:03,250 --> 00:02:05,876
Because the person imprisoned here doesn’t know if he will leave or not
